    "passives": {
      "IamtheQueenPassiveAVictoriaRegular": {
        "id": "IamtheQueenPassiveAVictoriaRegular",
        "found": true,
        "localization": {
          "name": "Crowned Étoile",
          "description": "This unit cannot be defeated by damage from Poison or Burn status effects.\n\nThis unit cannot fall asleep or be sent to the reinforcements from the battlefield.\n\nThis unit's attacks will not wake sleeping enemies, and heal this unit for 100% of total damage dealt.\n\nWhenever another ally takes damage from an attack, this unit will immediately get the turn by having its TU reduced to 0. This extra turn may be interrupted by other effects that influence the turn order (e.g. other stuns targeting the lowest TU target). Then this effect cannot trigger again until 50TU advances.\n\nIf this unit has another ally on the battlefield, whenever this unit takes damage from an attack and survives until after the end of the turn, this unit grants a random enemy the Deep Sleep status effect for 100TU, even if they have already slept while on the battlefield. This is not a Skin passive skill.\n\nDeep Sleep will overwrite other status effects, cannot be overwritten by Burn or Sleep status effects, and cannot be Purified."
        }
      },
      "WarQueenPassiveAVictoriaRegular": {
        "id": "WarQueenPassiveAVictoriaRegular",
        "found": true,
        "localization": {
          "name": "Queen's Grace",
          "description": "This unit enters battle with 10% HP Regen for 200TU, a Power Charge and an Instant Death Ward. This unit has 80% damage reduction from attacks for 100TU.\n\nIf this unit would be defeated while it has a Power Charge, it instead survives with 1 HP and then cannot be defeated until its next turn. The Power Charge will be consumed when this effect is triggered.\n\nWhenever this unit defeats a non-conjured enemy with an attack, all allies on the battlefield are healed for 100% of their max HP, and granted an Instant Death Ward.\n\nEach time an ally (including this unit) gets the turn, this unit will become Purified (negative status effects like sleep, burn or poison are removed) at the end of that turn.\n\nEach time an enemy gets the turn, this unit will become Enraged at the end of that turn. An Enraged unit's attack is increased to 1.5x until the end of their next turn. Enrage will overwrite any existing Weak or Enrage effects on this unit.\n\nAn Instant Death Ward prevents this unit from being immediately defeated without damage by a non-boss enemy once, then is removed. Instant Death Wards cannot be ignored and cannot stack. A unit with 10% HP Regen will heal for 10% of their max HP after every turn. HP Regen effects will overwrite existing HP Regen effects. Power Charges can be consumed by certain skills to activate or enhance their effects. Power Charges will be removed if this unit leaves the battlefield. Power Charges cannot stack."
        }
      },
